The fifth harm: when one’s mysterious charts are revealed or one receives precious scriptures, or when one encounters a numinous master who imparts divine texts—yet fails to follow the precepts and covenants, outwardly leaking celestial perfection, and before completing nine years of practice, presents petitions to sacred mountains, causing the Azure Palace to record one’s name and the Golden Tower to compile one’s deeds, then transmits these to others, scattering them among the world—such reckless disclosure of the true and leakage of the sacred will bring retribution upon oneself. Though one may bear a transcendent name, it will instead burden the Seven Mysteries. The Dao of immortality ascends on high, while one’s body perishes in the nether springs, forever consigned to ghostly reckoning, never to be absolved through ten thousand kalpas.

The sixth harm: when the body lingers in defilement and impurity, the numinous barrier loses its radiance, the Five Spirits scatter and flee, the Red Child soars away, and demonic forces assail one from within and without—both inner and outer are lost. With such learning, one’s aspirations to attainment only invite harm. The Perfected Immortals ascend in solitude, while one sinks into turbid chaos, and immortality remains forever beyond reach.

The seventh harm: consuming the flesh of the six livestock, slaughtering creatures with hooves and mouths for their savor, filling the viscera with foul qi, inflicting death’s punishment upon the innocent, disturbing the true qi at the numinous gate, startling the wandering spirits of the Red Child, causing the hun and po to wander the chambers, and clogging the mouth and teeth with turbid stagnation. The Perfected Immortals ascend to the Jade Clarity, while one’s own body founders in the earthly realm. Though one may bear a transcendent name in the Emperor’s records, this will not exempt one from inevitable death.

The Most High Sagely Thearch declares: The foundation of learning lies in urgently guarding against the seven harms. Once one has gazed upon the gates of the cavern-heavens and perused the jade scriptures, if one does not transgress the prohibitions of the seven harms, one may sit and await the descent of the numinous, ascending at dawn into the light of day.

If one toils externally in study yet fails to dispel the seven harms within, this will lead to attainment turning into failure, life into death, fortune into misfortune, and flight into sinking. The numinous immortals wander the lofty clarity, while the Five Spirits scatter to the eight wilds. The Red Child wails within the central chamber, and the wandering soul laments in the dark emptiness.

Thus, the path to immortality has its successes and failures, and superior learning entails the seven harms. Those who earnestly revere the Dao must thoroughly refine their true nature.

All who are divinely endowed and aligned with the charts, whose jade embryos dwell in the Purple Void, whose names are inscribed in the Eastern Florescence—having beheld the text on the examination of the seven harms—if they possess no such endowment, may not rashly peruse the numinous scriptures or casually view the sacred texts. Those who encounter this text are of a nature harmonious with transcendence; after nine years of cultivation, they may attain flight through the mysterious void and ascend to the Jade Clarity of the Highest Heaven.

Recite the precepts beginning from the fifth, proceeding in order to the end and then returning to the start, completing one cycle at the fourth, without reading the prefaces or postscripts. As the text is lengthy and not repeated, refer to separate scrolls when reciting.

Upon completing the recitation of the precepts, rise and approach the lamp, strike the teeth three times, and silently recite the Lamp-Brightening Incantation three times:

The Most High scatters light in the ten directions,
Flowering lamps convey sincerity.
All heavens blaze resplendent,
All earths shine with clarity.
My body, too, becomes luminous,
The five viscera blossom with splendor.
Fiery radiance illumines the Great Void,
Far-reaching thoughts flourish in the Jade Clarity.

Cinnabar essence abides in the Great Origin,
Mysterious intestines resound in emptiness.
Embracing form, eradicating the roots of suffering,
Contemplating the profound and true.
Hanging blossoms reveal no substance,
Causal conditions manifest as light and image.
My body is likewise transformed,
Riding transformation, entrusting to the flowing radiance.

Night’s light reveals the yang elixir,
Shining brightly in the numinous chamber.
All lamps universally radiate brilliance,
All yin is extinguished.
My spirit, too, becomes keen and bright,
Ever delighting in wisdom and insight.
Carefree, I follow the Dao’s course,
Changing and yielding to heaven’s decree.

Raising my form, I tread the empty cavern,
Night’s candle gleams with flowing splendor.

When the incantation is finished, turn from west to east, return the incense burner, and recite the incantation to clear the throat before retiring to the chamber, observing all movements as in the morning rites.

At dawn the next day, at the hour of *chou*, rise with solemn purity. At the hour of *yin*, ascend the platform to the door, clear the throat, recite the incantation, and visualize the master—all as in the morning rites.

For those who have not taken a worldly master and seek to invoke the mysterious covenant, visualize the Azure Lad of the Mysterious Master in the Palace of the Square Cauldron, beseeching his descent and manifestation, □ the secret of longevity, and swift attainment of immortality, that the dissemination of transformation may be boundless.

Upon completing the visualization of the master, close the eyes, strike the teeth thirty-six times, and recite the incantation:

Before the Great Demon King of the Northern Thearch,
Before the Lord Who Receives Affairs,
Ghosts of the Yellow Springs’ bends,
The Four Luminaries of Mount Feng,
A thousand demons mingling forms,
Nine-headed beings sharing one body,
Divine tigers releasing venom,
Decapitating with thunderous might,
True tones of the divine lords,
Uttering curses of execution,
No kinship with the Great Tenuity,
Yet by command they seize and record.
Mountains and rivers ring with bells,
Intertwining radiance flows and flashes.
Nine heavens’ winds and fires,
Wield the divine blades of subjugation.
Ten trials of the inauspicious,
Subduing and extinguishing the myriad spirits.
Should any demonic toxin dare rise,
It shall be sealed within the Three Passes.
I invoke the cavernous laws—
Let none disobey these words.

Upon completion, strike the teeth thirty-six times again, open the incense burner, and strike the teeth once more.

When the incense burner is opened, kneel facing north (or sit slightly), strike the teeth thirty-six times, and summon the officials:

With reverence, I summon from within the body of your servant [Name]—from the four limbs, five constituents, Jade Gate, Purple Chamber, and thirty-nine portals of the Upper Perfected—
the numinous officials of the left and right flying immortals,
the Jade Clarity Attendants,
the Five Emperors and Five-Colored Primordial August Perfected,
the Flying Dragon Merit Clerks,
the Divine Immortal Envoys—
thirty-six of each.

The Jade Clarity Attendants wield the feathered tablets of the flying immortals, their nine-colored banners illuminating the heavens;
The Five Emperors and Five-Colored Primordial August Perfected hold the life-controlling demonic banners of the Five Emperors;
The Flying Dragon Merit Clerks, adorned in feathered robes and golden true phoenix insignia;
The Divine Immortal Envoys, intertwining the Seven Origins, bearing jade tablets, standing before your servant—
they receive the secret words from your servant’s mouth, ascend the golden root, purple canopy, cinnabar shafts, and jade carriage of flying clouds’ wheels, accompanied by twelve Golden Immortals and Jade Lads, twelve Great Flower Jade Maidens, twenty-four myriad hosts of left and right dragon-tiger soaring feathered riders, flying through the Purple Void, ascending to the Golden Tower Jade Palace, the jasper chambers and cinnabar halls within the nine heavens above.

They ascend to report to the Supreme, Boundless, and Utmost Cavern-True Nine Mysteries Primordial Father;
the Great Void Mysterious Mother;
the Primordial Heavenly Thearch;
the Most High Jade Clarity Myriad Dao Venerable;
the King of the Immeasurable Heaven of Yu Shan;
the King of the Utmost Good Immeasurable Longevity Heaven;
the King of Xu Yan Heaven;
the King of Silent Heaven;
the King of Unarrogant Joy Heaven;
the King of Responsive Transformation Heaven;
the King of Brahma Treasure Heaven;
the King of Brahma Kama Heaven;
the King of Pari-Dhava Heaven;
the seventy-four Heavenly Thearchs;
the thirty-six Heavenly Kings;
the thirty-six Earthly Sovereigns;
the Venerable of the Myriad Origins;
the Jade Lads of the Three Heavens;
the Nine Heavens’ Chancellor, the Perfected King of Great Truth;
the thirty-nine Highest Emperors;
the twenty-four Jade Thearchs;
the Venerable of the Mysterious Antiquity;
the Venerable of the Myriad Origins;
the Most High Jade Dawn, the Great Dao Lord of the Supreme;
the Golden Tower Thearch of the Later Saints;
the Divine King of Fusang’s Yang Valley;
the Four Controllers and Five Emperors;
the Southern Culmen’s Upper Prime Lord of Prohibitions;
the Western Terrace’s Tortoise Mother;
the Jade Guardian King of the Supreme Clarity;
the Highest Minister of Destiny, the Great Controller of the Dawn;
the Azure Lad of the Jade Gate of the Eastern Sea;
the Great Dao of the Supreme Three Heavens of the Great Void of Tai Qing;
the Most High Lord Lao;
the Most High Venerable;
the Heavenly Thearch Lord;
the Lord of the Nine Heavens’ Immortal Capital;
the Venerable of the Nine Qi—
the hundred thousand myriad layers of Dao qi,
the twelve hundred official lords,
the Four Perfected of the Supreme Polarity beneath the Jade Steps of Tai Qing,
the countless Highest August Perfected of the Dao,
the Heavenly Worthy of the Boundless—
the qi of the natural Mysterious Capital’s Primordial August.

